3:46Z","body":"> I applied the patch locally and found out that \"broken pipe\" is the reason for the errors\r\n\r\nAh! Maybe we could detect that error and not call Error if it is that?","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rclone/rclone/issues/comments/533807048/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"ncw","id":536803,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUzNjgwMw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/536803?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw","html_url":"https://github.com/ncw","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ncw/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rclone/rclone/issues/comments/533880035","html_url":"https://github.com/rclone/rclone/issues/3559#issuecomment-533880035","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rclone/rclone/issues/3559","id":533880035,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDUzMzg4MDAzNQ==","user":{"login":"riptl","id":21371810,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIxMzcxODEw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/21371810?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/riptl","html_url":"https://github.com/riptl","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/riptl/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/riptl/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/riptl/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/riptl/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/riptl/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/riptl/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/riptl/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/riptl/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/riptl/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2019-09-22T13:00:43Z","updated_at":"2019-09-22T13:00:49Z","body":"> Maybe we could detect that error and not call Error if it is that?\r\n\r\n@ncw As soon as the template starts a write on the underlying `http.ResponseWriter`, `res.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)` gets automatically called. That means `serve.Error` should only be called if no writes were made. Here's an example how to detect this with a custom `io.Writer`: https://github.com/rclone/rclone/pull/3560#issuecomment-533713097\r\n\r\nOtherwise, we could render the template to a buffer first and call `serve.Error` if the template execution failed, as implemented in #3560.","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rclone/rclone/issues/comments/533880035/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"riptl","id":21371810,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIxMzcxODEw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/21371810?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/riptl","html_url":"https://github.com/riptl","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/riptl/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/riptl/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/riptl/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/riptl/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscripti